        "email": "arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com",
        "username": "arshad512"
      },
      "date": "2020-01-01 12:31:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n>On a 32-bit host, you have changed the size of this union from 56 bytes to 44 bytes. Are you sure you want to do that?\nNeil, it was my fault. I did not consider 32bit at all. I will revert the changes.\n\n>The point of the \"space\" member is to consume space so that the struct is large enough to hold the various different callback data structures.  Since these are not checked regularly on i386, it is possible hit some problems there, but they could also be found and fixed easily at compile time.\nAndreas, yes. I have incorporated your review under the comments where we are introducing a new #define  \n\n>It would be useful to list some of the users\nI am trying this out. You should see this in the next patch push.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
